cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.CR

This paper deals with building a robust classification system that can perform well under uncertain target operating conditions. This involves comparing the performance of different classifiers across various metrics such as accuracy, expected cost, lift, precision, recall, and workforce utilization. The method used for this comparison is based on ROC analysis, decision analysis, and computational geometry. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
